I've thought of writing a blog about my experiences/views watching Dance Moms.  From the very start, I've enjoyed it although as time has gone on, the drama has increased and with it I've wondered if any is manufactured for the camera.  After watching it for the 2nd time on Amazon Instant Video, I don't think so and here's why:  if you watch the smoke before the fire episode where the moms and Abby talk with the executive producer, the drama is as (or perhaps even more so) than what is shown on regular episodes.  I could talk on and on about how and where and why it's so intense but I want to leave some for the viewer's (cringe) enjoyment.  I will say this - there's no hero here - not really one dance mom one could totally cheer for.  And as for Ms. Abby Lee Miller, let's just say that I had a band director who reminded me a great deal of her and I loved him.  She does some very questionable things but her eye for technique, from what I can tell, is dead on and as a music teacher myself, technique has to come first before ANYTHING.  I cheer for the moms occasionally and I never cheer for Abby when she's holding the children responsible for their moms' behavior.  For chrissake, they're all under age - Brooke is the only one who could really stand up to her mother as I had to do to mine when I was in band in high school.  The others are truly not in control of their destiny in most ways.  And by the way, shooting a movie in Hollywood does NOT make a child more outstanding than the other, Ms. Abby.  If you watch these episodes, you'll see what I'm talking about."
