It's been a very long time since I was actually excited about a TV show. Usually, shows I watch just sort of reach a level of pleasant/better than the majority of crap that's out there. Continuum has virtually everything I love in a good show though. Strong female lead, witty sidekick, great worldbuilding, believable action within the universe that they've created, sympathetic villains, a plot and issues that go beyond solving the week's case, and tight writing. I can't wait until this is available in the States. I will buy as many seasons as come out and try to support the show as best I can. Quality programming, writing, acting.**I should add that after watching the pilot, I went and watched the entirety of season 1 (all 10 episodes) in under two days. I just couldn't stop myself. It's that good."
