This review refers to \"Building Pharaoh's Chariot.\" If you are interested in Ancient history, warfare, or inventions, you will enjoy this Nova episode. Experts recreate Ancient Egyptian chariots and harness, using one from King Tut's tomb and wall paintings, then test them. In the Bronze Age, Egyptians refined the heavy chariots of the other Near Eastern empires into fast, light, and well sprung vehicles that could be driven at a gallop and rain arrows on an enemy in a rapid approach and wheel attack. A must see for ancient military enthusiasts."
